cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CV 

The paper deals with the problem of principal component analysis (PCA) which is a popular technique in machine learning, data analysis, signal and image processing, and others. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a novel method for dimension estimation which involves random matrix perturbation theory ideas, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper mentions applications in signal and image processing, which could place it in cs.SI (Signal Processing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
